        "label": "OAuth app client credentials",
        "generateUrl": "https://developers.grain.com/",
        "setup": "For integrations used by any Grain users, request/register a Grain OAuth client to obtain a `client_id` and, for server-side apps, a `client_secret`. Grain's docs say these credentials are obtained manually and require a registered redirect URI prefix; browser apps can also register CORS origins. Then send users to `https://grain.com/_/public-api/oauth2/authorize` and exchange the returned code at `https://api.grain.com/_/public-api/oauth2/token`. PKCE (`code_challenge_method=S256`) is supported and required for client-side-only auth."
